  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Based on pilot patient observations,the investigators anticipate that chronic fatigue
      syndrome (CFS) patients may benefit from B-cell depletion therapy.

      The hypothesis is that at least a subset of CFS patients have an activated immune system
      involving B-lymphocytes, and that B-cell depletion may alleviate symptoms.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
